workflow.name: Sync Google Calendar events to Google Sheets with Slack notifications
workflow.description:
Sync your Google Calendar events with Google Sheets and get daily Slack summaries with meeting statistics.
FEATURES:

Real-time sync of new and updated events
Auto-categorization (Meeting, 1:1, Interview, Demo, Focus Time)
Platform detection (Google Meet, Zoom, Teams)
Daily statistics dashboard
Cancellation tracking
Optional email notifications to attendees

FLOWS:

New Event: Log to Sheets + Slack notification + Optional email
Updated Event: Update Sheets + Slack notification
Canceled Event: Log cancellation + Slack alert
Daily Summary (8AM): Meeting time stats + Schedule to Slack

SETUP:

Connect Google account with Calendar access
Create Google Sheet with 3 tabs:

Events: ID, Synced At, Title, Category, Date, Day, Start Time, End Time, Duration, Platform, Attendees, Status, Meeting Link
Cancellations: ID, Canceled At, Title, Original Date, Original Time, Affected Attendees
Statistics: Date, Total Events, Meeting Time, Minutes, Busy %, Status, Virtual, In-Person


Replace YOUR_DOCUMENT_ID in all Sheets nodes
Connect Slack (#calendar, #errors channels)
Optional: Connect Gmail for attendee notifications

DAILY STATISTICS:

Total events count
Time spent in meetings
Busy percentage of work day
Virtual vs in-person breakdown
Full day schedule

IDEAL FOR:
Anyone wanting to track their calendar, analyze meeting patterns, or get daily schedule summaries on Slack.

parameters.content:
## Sync Google Calendar events to Sheets with Slack notifications

Automatically track all calendar events, log them to Google Sheets, and send Slack notifications.

### How it works

1. **Monitor** - Watches calendar for new and updated events
2. **Process** - Extracts title, date, time, attendees, platform
3. **Categorize** - Auto-tags: Meeting, 1:1, Interview, Demo, Focus
4. **Log** - Saves all events to Google Sheets
5. **Alert** - Slack notifications for changes and cancellations
6. **Report** - Daily 8 AM summary with stats

### Setup steps

1. Connect Google Calendar, Google Sheets, Slack, Gmail
2. Create Sheet with tab named "Events"
3. Replace YOUR_DOCUMENT_ID in Sheets nodes
4. Configure Slack channels: #calendar and #errors
5. Test by creating a calendar event

## Step 1: Calendar Triggers

**What happens here:**
- New event trigger
- Updated event trigger
- Monitors your calendar

## Step 2: Event Processing

**What happens here:**
- Extract event details
- Check if cancelled
- Route accordingly

## Step 3: Logging & Alerts

**What happens here:**
- Log to Sheets
- Slack notifications
- Track changes

## Step 4: Confirmation Email

**What happens here:**
- Prepare email
- Send to attendees
- Confirmation flow

## Step 5: Daily Summary

**What happens here:**
- 8 AM trigger
- Calculate statistics
- Slack report

## Step 6: Error Handling

**What happens here:**
- Catch errors
- Format details
- Alert #errors

data.details:
The IF node can be used to implement binary conditional logic in your workflow. You can set up one-to-many conditions to evaluate each item of data being inputted into the node. That data will either evaluate to TRUE or FALSE and route out of the node accordingly.

This node has multiple types of conditions: Bool, String, Number, and Date & Time.
